Defendant Jasma S Jackson in court with attorney Daniel P. Murray.  Pablo Galaviz appeared for the State of Wisconsin.   Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count 16.  Court finds defendant guilty.


Court orders the following: 
Ct. 16:
- Total sentence: 2 years (Initial Confinement: 1 year , Extended Supervision: 1 year)  Stayed for 1 year Probation
- Fine totaling $530 to be paid as a Condition of Probation 
- Restitution of $577.00 for extradition fees to the DA's Office to be paid as a Condition of Probation.
- Conditions of  Probation:  Follow thru with any treatment/counseling recommended by Agent.   Any valid prescription drugs must be taken only in the manner in which they are prescribed; Inform Agent of all prescriptions. Maintain full-time employment and/or combination of schooling.   No contact with co-defendants or victims or any Pick n' Save.   Defendant to provide DNA sample, if not yet provided.  DNA, surcharge is waived. 
-  10 days jail Condition Time (nonworking hours) STAYED to be used at the Agents discretion. Huber/Straight time to be used at the Agents discretion. Twelve days credit.

Defendant Jasma S Jackson in court with attorney Daniel P. Murray.  Michele W. Hulgaard appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Defense has received an offer but needs more time for a plea/sentencing and requests another date in 30 days. Court grants request.  Hearing scheduled for May 22, 2015 at 11:00 am.
Plea/sentencing hearing on April 20, 2015 at 01:30 pm.
Defendant waives his/her right to a Preliminary Hearing.

Defendant Jasma S Jackson in court with attorney Daniel P. Murray.   District Attorney's Office Law Intern appeared for the State of Wisconsin.   NOT GUILTY PLEA ENTERED.  Plea/sentencing hearing scheduled for April 20, 2015 at 01:30 pm.

Defendant not to possess any drug paraphernalia.  Defendant to have no contact with codefendants/victim/witness/pharmacies listed in the Criminal Complaint.

An attorney will be appointed.  Court tolled time limits for preliminary hearing.  Hearing scheduled for April 6, 2015 at 10:00 am.
